    detailedExplanationExpert: `Standard form: M–P: All C are L (A). S–M: No C are R (E). Conclusion: Some L are not R (O). Both universal, conclusion particular. The O-conclusion asserts existence. The E-premise actually states C is not confirmed real, yet the conclusion treats C as non-empty. Existential Fallacy under Boolean interpretation.`,
    questionFormat: "standard"
